1
00:00:05,518 --> 00:00:09,943
‘Non-envious’, the inversion of that
is to show some honour;

2
00:00:09,943 --> 00:00:12,733
some appreciation;
some respect. 

3
00:00:12,886 --> 00:00:15,453
And not just formal—

4
00:00:15,453 --> 00:00:18,725
I’m not talking 
about formal respect.

5
00:00:18,725 --> 00:00:23,694
Using this kind of 
an honourific title and not that:

6
00:00:23,709 --> 00:00:27,722
that is formal,
the formal aspects of respect—

7
00:00:27,985 --> 00:00:29,861
[Substance Over Form]

8
00:00:30,107 --> 00:00:33,282
‘what will come first, 
what will come second’.

9
00:00:33,282 --> 00:00:35,727
We’re interested 
in the substantial

10
00:00:35,727 --> 00:00:41,433
heartfelt appreciation 
of the devotion of others—

11
00:00:42,541 --> 00:00:45,729
not formalist formalities;

12
00:00:45,729 --> 00:00:50,921
that someone didn’t observe
some formality,

13
00:00:51,033 --> 00:00:55,213
they violated a technicality.

14
00:00:56,230 --> 00:00:58,641
No one will be dismissed 
from Kṛṣṇa consciousness

15
00:00:58,641 --> 00:01:02,501
for violating a technicality.

16
00:01:05,429 --> 00:01:12,316
Rather, the rāga-bhaktas, 
they’re celebrated

17
00:01:12,710 --> 00:01:14,862
for ignoring those formalities.

18
00:01:14,862 --> 00:01:16,840
Once, Guru Mahārāj said,

19
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:19,948
“When Yaśodā
is whipping Kṛṣṇa:

20
00:01:19,948 --> 00:01:24,546
no ‘Oṁ Viṣṇupād Paramahaṁsa’;

21
00:01:24,546 --> 00:01:25,553
she’s running after Kṛṣṇa

22
00:01:25,553 --> 00:01:28,043
and Kṛṣṇa 
is running from her,

23
00:01:28,043 --> 00:01:33,830
and His mascara 
is running down His face.

24
00:01:33,830 --> 00:01:41,663
Gopy ādade Tvayi kṛtāgasi dāma tāvad
yā Te daśāśru-kalilāñjana-sambhramākṣam:

25
00:01:41,663 --> 00:01:45,747
Kuntī’s saying, “How beautifully bewildering 
this vision is.

26
00:01:45,747 --> 00:01:50,283
Whom fear personified
is scared to death of,

27
00:01:50,283 --> 00:01:52,594
that Kṛṣṇa, is running, crying,

28
00:01:52,594 --> 00:01:56,535
His mascara running down 
His lotus face

29
00:01:56,535 --> 00:01:59,361
making it even more beautiful,

30
00:01:59,361 --> 00:02:03,469
and Mother Yaśodā’s 
running after Him.” (SB: 1.8.31)

31
00:02:03,469 --> 00:02:09,985
Not interested in 
the formal Absolute, formality,

32
00:02:09,985 --> 00:02:15,304
but substance.
And substance means devotion. 

33
00:02:15,304 --> 00:02:20,022
So, there, we need
to give recognition

34
00:02:20,022 --> 00:02:22,735
to the devotion of others.

35
00:02:22,735 --> 00:02:24,421
Rūpa Goswāmī says that in

36
00:02:24,421 --> 00:02:28,169
Bhakti-rasāmṛta-sindhu
—the book of devotion—

37
00:02:28,169 --> 00:02:30,369
that one of the symptoms
of a devotee is that

38
00:02:30,369 --> 00:02:32,249
they’re always appreciating 
the good qualities

39
00:02:32,249 --> 00:02:33,977
of another devotee.

40
00:02:33,977 --> 00:02:37,935
So when Nārada is approaching 
all those devotees

41
00:02:37,935 --> 00:02:40,278
in the first part of
the Bṛhad-bhāgavatāmṛtam,

42
00:02:40,278 --> 00:02:41,486
every time he praises one,

43
00:02:41,486 --> 00:02:43,054
they praise someone else

44
00:02:43,054 --> 00:02:44,333
as being higher to them.

45
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:46,214
He goes to them, 
praises them,

46
00:02:46,214 --> 00:02:48,478
they praise someone else
as being higher.

47
00:02:48,478 --> 00:02:52,544
On and on and on … 
until what happens?

48
00:02:53,467 --> 00:02:59,653
Āsām aho charaṇa-reṇu-juṣām ahaṁ syāṁ
Vṛndāvane kim api gulma-latauṣadhīnām

49
00:02:59,653 --> 00:03:08,360
yā dustyajaṁ sva-janam ārya-pathaṁ cha hitvā
bhejur Mukunda-padavīṁ śrutibhir vimṛgyām (SB: 10.47.61).

50
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,821
That Uddhava …

51
00:03:09,836 --> 00:03:14,205
“Na tathā Me priyatama
ātma-yonir na Śaṅkaraḥ

52
00:03:14,205 --> 00:03:18,700
na cha saṅkarṣaṇo na śrīr
naivātmā cha yathā bhavān:

53
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:22,188
That Uddhava, who Kṛṣṇa says is “more dear
to Me than My own self” (SB: 11.14.15).

54
00:03:22,188 --> 00:03:26,782
He praises the dust 
of the lotus feet of

55
00:03:26,782 --> 00:03:31,031
Śrīmatī Rādhāṛāṇī
and the Vraja-gopīs.

56
00:03:31,031 --> 00:03:33,514
So then they’re established
as the great devotees,

57
00:03:33,514 --> 00:03:35,146
and what are they saying? 

58
00:03:35,146 --> 00:03:39,741
“Oh! How exalted is 
the soil of Vṛndāvan,

59
00:03:39,741 --> 00:03:42,901
the trees of Vṛndāvan!”

60
00:03:43,225 --> 00:03:46,008
They’re praising
all the śānta-rasa bhaktas.

61
00:03:46,008 --> 00:03:50,961
Chandravalī and her …, they’re saying, 
“This flute, what is this?

62
00:03:50,969 --> 00:03:56,731
A dry piece of wood 
with so many flaws or knots

63
00:03:56,731 --> 00:03:59,346
is capturing all the nectar
from Kṛṣṇa’s lips.

64
00:03:59,346 --> 00:04:00,722
What was meant for us gopīs,

65
00:04:00,738 --> 00:04:05,558
the flute has stolen that, indirectly.”

66
00:04:05,558 --> 00:04:08,835
That type of envy
Rūpa Goswāmī is celebrating

67
00:04:08,835 --> 00:04:13,899
in this śloka; 
but other than that: not. 

68
00:04:13,918 --> 00:04:16,727
Everyone they’re appreciating;

69
00:04:16,727 --> 00:04:19,008
the highest devotees 
are appreciating

70
00:04:19,008 --> 00:04:20,679
the position of those 
who appear to be

71
00:04:20,679 --> 00:04:22,840
in a lower position.

72
00:04:22,840 --> 00:04:25,537
That’s Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

73
00:04:25,537 --> 00:04:28,102
Where the inverse,

74
00:04:28,102 --> 00:04:32,841
the lower group, 
is offending the higher

75
00:04:34,170 --> 00:04:36,665
or not appreciating.

76
00:04:36,665 --> 00:04:38,685
But the actual higher devotees,

77
00:04:38,685 --> 00:04:41,379
they are appreciating
the devotion of even the lower. 

78
00:04:41,379 --> 00:04:43,282
Guru Mahārāj is saying, when

79
00:04:43,282 --> 00:04:47,071
the lady disciple of Swāmī Mahārāj

80
00:04:47,071 --> 00:04:49,814
in the Naṭ Mandir 
of Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh says,

81
00:04:49,814 --> 00:04:52,586
“What I like 
about Kṛṣṇa consciousness is that

82
00:04:52,586 --> 00:04:54,024
we’re being given a chance

83
00:04:54,024 --> 00:04:56,566
to have a family life with Kṛṣṇa”,

84
00:04:56,566 --> 00:04:59,158
Guru Mahārāj
quoted that for thirty years

85
00:04:59,158 --> 00:05:03,130
as something
that touched his heart.

86
00:05:03,130 --> 00:05:05,363
He’s appreciating 
what she expressed.

87
00:05:05,363 --> 00:05:06,867
When Achyutānanda said

88
00:05:06,867 --> 00:05:08,768
he hadn’t eaten for three days

89
00:05:08,768 --> 00:05:12,693
because some Mahārāj 
left with the key to the food,

90
00:05:12,693 --> 00:05:16,254
he came to the Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh
for a little prasād,

91
00:05:16,254 --> 00:05:20,636
and Gurudev and Guru Mahārāj
found out. They were mortified,

92
00:05:20,729 --> 00:05:23,043
and said, “Why didn’t you come?”

93
00:05:23,043 --> 00:05:27,907
And Achyutānanda said,
“Uh, Kṛṣṇa's dancing.”

94
00:05:27,922 --> 00:05:31,623
That melted the heart 
of Guru Mahārāj and Gurudev.

95
00:05:31,623 --> 00:05:34,422
Guru Mahārāj
told that story for 30 years.

96
00:05:34,422 --> 00:05:37,041
“Kṛṣṇa’s dancing.”

97
00:05:37,041 --> 00:05:42,118
He meant, if He’s dancing and
so many are being thrown

98
00:05:42,118 --> 00:05:43,714
this way and that way 
and trembled upon:

99
00:05:43,714 --> 00:05:45,931
Kṛṣṇs dancing; 
it’s gopī-bhāva.

100
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:52,309
That if He’s happy, 
then everything’s okay.

101
00:05:52,827 --> 00:05:55,468
I’m fasting for three days—
that’s not a problem;

102
00:05:55,468 --> 00:05:58,307
Kṛṣṇa’s dancing.

103
00:05:58,307 --> 00:06:00,515
So that, that was expressed 
from his heart,

104
00:06:00,515 --> 00:06:02,237
Guru Mahārāj and Gurudev

105
00:06:02,237 --> 00:06:03,975
are recognising 
some devotion there;

106
00:06:03,975 --> 00:06:06,078
they’re celebrating that. 

107
00:06:06,078 --> 00:06:07,969
That’s what giving honour is:

108
00:06:07,969 --> 00:06:10,971
not formalities, titles,

109
00:06:12,228 --> 00:06:17,171
and ‘first position, second position’—
this kind of thing;

110
00:06:17,171 --> 00:06:19,717
but recognition of 
substantial devotional qualities;

111
00:06:19,717 --> 00:06:24,704
tendencies; expressions;
sevā; service—those things.

112
00:06:24,704 --> 00:06:30,357
That’s a meaningful way
to give some recognition. 

